SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 371
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to recognize Kathy Jones-Terry, Hamblen
County Chancery and Probate Court Clerk and
Master, on the occasion of her retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
years of public service; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable person is Kathy Jones-Terry, who, having admirably
served the citizens of Hamblen County as Chancery and Probate Court County Clerk and
Master since 1995, is taking a much-deserved retirement this year; and
WHEREAS, after a one-year stint as an interviewer with the Hamblen County
Department of Human Services, Kathy Jones-Terry taught English and journalism at
Morristown-Hamblen West High School from 1982 to 1995; and
WHEREAS, in becoming the clerk and master of the Hamblen County Chancery and
Probate Court in 1995, she followed in the footsteps of her mother, Jean Wolfe Jones, who held
the post for thirty years immediately prior to the start of Kathy Jones-Terry's nearly thirty-year
tenure; and
WHEREAS, during her time as clerk and master, she has served three chancellors,
created and maintained a clerk and master public website for court information and payment of
delinquent taxes, and transitioned her office to online delinquent tax sales as well as to e-filing
and permanent digital storage of all Chancery and Probate Court records for Hamblen County;
and
